first step in changing of build system

I've created a new folder (fr.univartois.ili.fsnet), this this the root folder of our project.
It should contains just a pom.xml and some folders that's represents each of subproject.

Also, i've created fr.univartois.ili.fsnet/entities/, this forlder include the java code and resources from
fr.univartois.ili.fsnet.entities.test AND fr.univartois.ili.fsnet.entities following defined maven project structure

So, if you want to build all subprojects you have to :
cd $somewhere$/fr.univartois.ili.fsnet/
mvn package

if you want to juste build a part of our project you have to
cd $somewhere$/fr.univartois.ili.fsnet/$partOfOurProject$
mvn package

For example, to build the entities part you should execute :
cd $somewhere$/fr.univartois.ili.fsnet/entities
mvn package

(Please be sure that you have configured a mysql database following the
fr.univartois.ili.fsnet/entities/src/main/resources/META-INF/persistence.xml
configuration file ...)

Finally, to import entities subproject in Eclipse you have to :
1. let maven download for you all of project dependencies by running a first build (see above) ^^
2. open eclipse
3. right click on project explorer
4. import -> general -> existing project into workspace
5. select the entities directory using browse button
6. click on finish
7. windows -> preferences -> java -> buildpath -> classpath variables -> new
Name: M2_REPO
Path: select the ~/.m2/repository folder by clicking on Folder button
